                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.003/155</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum by the Secretary of State of a Conversation With
                        the Japanese Ambassador</hi> (<hi rend="italic">Debuchi</hi>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-09-14">September 14,
                            1929</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>When the Ambassador called I asked him if there was anything new in the
                    China-Japan situation with regard to extraterritoriality. He told me that China
                    claimed to have annulled the extraterritoriality rights of Japan but that Japan
                    had not admitted it.</p>
            </div>
